# 🌐 Advanced HTML Projects Repository (Medium → High Level)

This contains **15 medium to high-level HTML projects** designed to strengthen practical web development skills and help build real-world frontend layouts using only HTML (and minimal structural styling where needed).

---

## 🎯 Purpose of This Repository

The main goal of this repository is to move beyond basic HTML and focus on **structured, real-world webpage building**. These projects help learners understand how actual websites are planned and structured using HTML.

By practicing these projects, you will improve your ability to:
- Design multi-section web pages
- Create multi-page websites using linking
- Build structured layouts like dashboards and blogs
- Handle forms with proper input types and validation attributes
- Understand semantic HTML structure used in real projects

---

## 📚 List of Advanced HTML Projects

1. Multi-page Portfolio Website (with navigation and sections)  
2. Professional Resume / CV Webpage Layout  
3. E-commerce Product Detail Page  
4. Multi-section Landing Page (Hero, Features, Footer)  
5. Form with HTML Validation (required, email, number constraints)  
6. Survey / Feedback Form with structured inputs  
7. Blog Page with Sidebar Layout  
8. Navigation Bar with Dropdown Menu Structure  
9. Advanced Table Layout (rowspan, colspan usage)  
10. Image Gallery Grid Layout  
11. Embedded Google Map Page  
12. Login and Signup UI Pages (linked structure)  
13. Event Invitation Webpage  
14. Pricing Table Layout (plans and comparison)  
15. Simple Admin Dashboard Layout (sidebar + main content)

---

## 🧠 What You Will Learn

After completing these projects, you will gain a strong understanding of:

- Real-world HTML page structuring  
- Semantic layout design (header, section, article, aside, footer)  
- Multi-page website navigation  
- Form design with validation basics  
- Table structuring for data representation  
- UI layout thinking (how websites are visually organized)  
- Building portfolio-ready frontend projects  

